narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: - An introduction to a number of critical modernist texts and their relevance to European imperialism. - Debates within literary theory and criticism and how they have evolved

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: The breadth of the course is its main strength. Over the course of the semester, we had the opportunity of discussing and debating a series of critical texts in their historical contexts. It was a also a good combination of theory, history and literature. Its interdisciplinary approach made for great discussion.

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: Whole heartedly I claim that this course is the most interesting offered at yale.
